About Trivy
Trivy is an open-source security scanner developed by Aqua Security. It is used to detect:
-> Vulnerabilities in OS packages and software dependencies.
-> Misconfigurations in Infrastructure as Code (IaC) like Kubernetes, Dockerfiles, Terraform, and CloudFormation.
-> Sensitive data (like hardcoded secrets).
-> Software Bill of Materials (SBOM) issues.
--------------------------
We can use Trivy for scanning the 
-> Container images
-> File systems
-> Git repositories
-> Kubernetes manifests
-> Terraform
-> SBOMs (Software Bill of Materials)
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
| Tool/Environment                    | Purpose                                           |
| ----------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------- |
| **Docker**                          | Image vulnerability scanning                      |
| **Kubernetes (k8s)**                | Scanning manifests and running workloads          |
| **Terraform/CloudFormation**        | Infrastructure as Code scanning                   |
| **GitHub Actions**                  | Automated scanning in CI pipelines                |
| **GitLab CI**                       | Security gate in GitLab pipelines                 |
| **Jenkins**                         | Scanning in custom pipeline stages                |
| **VS Code** (via extensions or CLI) | Developer-side scanning                           |
| **File System Scans**               | Scanning source code and app dependencies locally |
| **SBOM Scans**                      | Reviewing known components and vulnerabilities    |
-------------------------------------- ---------------------------------------------------
How to use : 
1. 🐳 Docker Images -> trivy image nginx:latest
2. 📁 File System or Source Code Projects -> trivy fs ./my-project
3. ☁️ IaC Tools (Terraform, Kubernetes, etc.) -> 
For Kubernetes -> trivy config ./k8s/
For Terraform -> trivy config ./terraform/
4. ✅ Software Bill of Materials (SBOM) Scanning -> trivy sbom sbom.json
5. ✅ Secrets Detection -> trivy fs --scanners secret .
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
For K8s : 
./k8s/deployment.yaml):
trivy config ./k8s/
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
-> trivy image 63eca18b382a
-> trivy image --severity HIGH,CRITICAL 63eca18b382a
-> trivy image -f json -o high.json --severity HIGH 63eca18b382a
-> trivy image -f table -o critical.txt --severity CRITICAL 63eca18b382a
-> trivy image --ignore-unfixed 63eca18b382a
-> trivy image --exit-code 0 63eca18b382a
-> trivy image -f json -o result.json --severity HIGH,CRITICAL --ignore-unfixed --exit-code 0 63eca18b382a
-> trivy image --exit-code 1 --ignore-unfixed 63eca18b382a (In case if we use this in pipline if it was not fixable it will igone)
============================================================================


